import Oseledets.Continuous.Flow
import Oseledets.Lyapunov.Extensions.Corollaries
import Oseledets.Cocycle.Norm

/-!
# Reduction of the continuous-flow MET to the discrete theorem

At integer times the continuous-flow Oseledets multiplicative ergodic theorem reduces to the
discrete-time theorem `Oseledets.oseledets_filtration'`.

The continuous-flow data is a measure-preserving flow `ŌÜ` (`Oseledets.MeasurePreservingFlow`)
and a continuous-time linear cocycle `A` over it (`Oseledets.FlowCocycle`). The reduction
identity `Oseledets.FlowCocycle.toCocycle_eq` shows that at integer times the continuous-time
cocycle equals the discrete iterated cocycle generated by its time-`1` map `A 1` over the
time-`1` flow map `ŌÜ 1`. Hence, once the discrete MET is applied to the generator `A 1` and the
dynamics `ŌÜ 1`, an Oseledets filtration for the integer-time continuous cocycle is obtained.

The additional ingredient is the integrability of the time-`1` log-norms. The discrete theorem
requires `log‚Āļ ‚ÄĖA 1‚ÄĖ ‚ąą L¬Ļ(őľ)` and `log‚Āļ ‚ÄĖ(A 1)‚ĀĽ¬Ļ‚ÄĖ ‚ąą L¬Ļ(őľ)`; these follow from a
uniform-on-`[0,1]` integrable dominating function for the continuous family, which is the
natural continuous-flow hypothesis (a continuous-time analogue of the discrete one-sided
integrability assumption).

## Main results

* `Oseledets.integrableLogNorm_timeOne`: the time-`1` map `A 1` has integrable positive
  log-norm, given an integrable function dominating `log‚Āļ ‚ÄĖA s‚ÄĖ` uniformly for `s ‚ąą [0,1]`.
* `Oseledets.integrableLogNorm_timeOne_inv`: the analogous statement for the inverse `(A 1)‚ĀĽ¬Ļ`.
* `Oseledets.exists_isOseledetsFiltration_timeOne`: the discrete MET applied to the time-`1`
  data, yielding an Oseledets filtration for the generator `A 1` over the dynamics `ŌÜ 1`.
-/

open MeasureTheory
open scoped Matrix.Norms.L2Operator

namespace Oseledets

variable {X : Type*} [MeasurableSpace X] {d : ‚Ąē} {őľ : Measure X}

/-- The positive part of the logarithm is measurable (`log‚Āļ = fun r => max 0 (log r)`). -/
private theorem measurable_posLog : Measurable Real.posLog :=
  measurable_const.max Real.measurable_log

/-- **Integrability of the time-`1` log-norm.** If an integrable function `g` dominates
`log‚Āļ ‚ÄĖA s‚ÄĖ` uniformly over `s ‚ąą [0,1]` (in particular at `s = 1`), then the time-`1` map
`A 1` of the continuous-time cocycle has integrable positive log-norm, i.e.
`IntegrableLogNorm (A 1 ¬∑) őľ`. This is exactly the discrete one-sided integrability hypothesis
for the generator `A 1`. -/
theorem integrableLogNorm_timeOne (ŌÜ : MeasurePreservingFlow őľ) (A : FlowCocycle ŌÜ d)
    {g : X ‚Üí ‚ĄĚ} (hg : Integrable g őľ)
    (hgb : ‚ąÄ s ‚ąą Set.Icc (0 : ‚ĄĚ) 1, ‚ąÄ x, Real.posLog ‚ÄĖA s x‚ÄĖ ‚Č§ g x) :
    IntegrableLogNorm (fun x => A 1 x) őľ := by
  refine hg.mono'
    (measurable_posLog.comp (measurable_l2_opNorm.comp (A.measurable 1))).aestronglyMeasurable
    (Filter.Eventually.of_forall fun x => ?_)
  rw [Real.norm_eq_abs, abs_of_nonneg (Real.posLog_nonneg)]
  exact hgb 1 (by norm_num [Set.mem_Icc]) x

/-- **Integrability of the time-`1` inverse log-norm.** If an integrable function `g'`
dominates `log‚Āļ ‚ÄĖ(A s)‚ĀĽ¬Ļ‚ÄĖ` uniformly over `s ‚ąą [0,1]` (in particular at `s = 1`), then the
inverse `(A 1)‚ĀĽ¬Ļ` of the time-`1` cocycle map has integrable positive log-norm, i.e.
`IntegrableLogNorm (fun x => (A 1 x)‚ĀĽ¬Ļ) őľ`. This is the discrete one-sided integrability
hypothesis for the inverse generator. -/
theorem integrableLogNorm_timeOne_inv (ŌÜ : MeasurePreservingFlow őľ) (A : FlowCocycle ŌÜ d)
    {g' : X ‚Üí ‚ĄĚ} (hg' : Integrable g' őľ)
    (hg'b : ‚ąÄ s ‚ąą Set.Icc (0 : ‚ĄĚ) 1, ‚ąÄ x, Real.posLog ‚ÄĖ(A s x)‚ĀĽ¬Ļ‚ÄĖ ‚Č§ g' x) :
    IntegrableLogNorm (fun x => (A 1 x)‚ĀĽ¬Ļ) őľ := by
  refine hg'.mono'
    (measurable_posLog.comp (measurable_l2_opNorm.comp
      (measurable_inv_matrix.comp (A.measurable 1)))).aestronglyMeasurable
    (Filter.Eventually.of_forall fun x => ?_)
  rw [Real.norm_eq_abs, abs_of_nonneg (Real.posLog_nonneg)]
  exact hg'b 1 (by norm_num [Set.mem_Icc]) x

/-- **Reduction of the continuous-flow MET to the discrete theorem at integer times.**
Applying the discrete Oseledets theorem `Oseledets.oseledets_filtration'` to the generator
`A 1` over the ergodic time-`1` dynamics `ŌÜ 1` yields an Oseledets filtration for the time-`1`
cocycle map. Combined with the reduction identity `Oseledets.FlowCocycle.toCocycle_eq` (which
identifies the integer-time continuous cocycle with the discrete iterated cocycle of `A 1` over
`ŌÜ 1`), this gives the integer-time behaviour of the continuous-flow cocycle.

The integrability hypotheses are stated as integrable dominating functions for the continuous
family `log‚Āļ ‚ÄĖA s‚ÄĖ` (resp. `log‚Āļ ‚ÄĖ(A s)‚ĀĽ¬Ļ‚ÄĖ`) uniformly over `s ‚ąą [0,1]`. -/
theorem exists_isOseledetsFiltration_timeOne [IsProbabilityMeasure őľ]
    (ŌÜ : MeasurePreservingFlow őľ) (herg : Ergodic (ŌÜ 1) őľ) (A : FlowCocycle ŌÜ d)
    {g g' : X ‚Üí ‚ĄĚ} (hg : Integrable g őľ) (hg' : Integrable g' őľ)
    (hgb : ‚ąÄ s ‚ąą Set.Icc (0 : ‚ĄĚ) 1, ‚ąÄ x, Real.posLog ‚ÄĖA s x‚ÄĖ ‚Č§ g x)
    (hg'b : ‚ąÄ s ‚ąą Set.Icc (0 : ‚ĄĚ) 1, ‚ąÄ x, Real.posLog ‚ÄĖ(A s x)‚ĀĽ¬Ļ‚ÄĖ ‚Č§ g' x) :
    ‚ąÉ (k : ‚Ąē) (lam : Fin k ‚Üí ‚ĄĚ)
      (V : Fin (k + 1) ‚Üí X ‚Üí Submodule ‚ĄĚ (EuclideanSpace ‚ĄĚ (Fin d))),
      IsOseledetsFiltration őľ (ŌÜ 1) (fun x => A 1 x) k lam V :=
  oseledets_filtration' herg (fun x => A 1 x) (fun x => A.det_ne_zero 1 x) (A.measurable 1)
    (integrableLogNorm_timeOne ŌÜ A hg hgb) (integrableLogNorm_timeOne_inv ŌÜ A hg' hg'b)

end Oseledets
